# HexAstral Microservices (services/*) Development Rules

**Loaded automatically when working under `services/`. Overrides root rules.**

---

## 1. Quick Facts

| Dimension | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Framework** | Hono 4.9+ |
| **Runtime** | Cloudflare Workers |
| **Access** | Service bindings only (internal) — no public routes |
| **Auth** | None (internal calls) |
| **Deploy** | wrangler deploy |
| **Local Port** | 3100+ (per service) |

---

## 2. Forbidden Patterns ❌

| Forbidden | Why | Alternative |
|-----------|-----|-------------|
| Direct external calls | No auth | Via hexastral-api service bindings only |
| Empty `catch {}` | Swallows errors | `logger.error(...)` + rethrow |
| `any` or `as Type` | Type loss | Zod parse or type guards |
| Long-running tasks (>30s) | Workers timeout | Use Workflows (core-workflow) |
| Store sensitive info | KV has no encryption | Workers AI, Vectorize, or external key management |

---

## 3. Service Overview

| Service | Port | Purpose | Endpoints |
|---------|------|---------|-----------|
| `svc-astro` | 3101 | Ba Zi / Zi Wei / Yi Jing computation | `/compute-*` |
| `svc-geocode` | 3103 | City / timezone lookup | `/geocode` |
| `svc-mailer` | 3104 | Transactional email (AWS SES) | `/send` |
| `svc-notify` | 3105 | Push notifications (Expo/FCM) | `/send`, `/send-fortune` |
| `svc-fortune` | 3106 | Daily fortune generation | `/generate`, queue handlers |
| `svc-admin-notify` | 3109 | Admin alerts (Telegram) | `/notify` |
| `svc-tail` | 3110 | Tail log aggregation | `/tail` |
| `svc-signal` | 3111 | Internal signal relay to API | `/signals/*` |

---

## 4. Route Design

### Entry Pattern

```typescript
import { Hono } from 'hono'
import { z } from 'zod/v4'
import { zValidator } from '@hono/zod-validator'

const app = new Hono()

// ✅ Simple POST endpoint
app.post('/compute-hehun', 
  zValidator('json', hehunSchema),
  async (c) => {
    const { person1, person2 } = c.req.valid('json')
    const result = computeHehun(person1, person2)
    return c.json(result)
  }
)

// ✅ Streaming response (large data)
app.get('/stream/:id', async (c) => {
  const { id } = c.req.param()
  return c.streamText(async (stream) => {
    for (const chunk of chunks) {
      await stream.write(chunk)
    }
  })
})

// ❌ Public route (no security)
// app.get('/public/endpoint')
```

### Input Validation

```typescript
const computeSchema = z.object({
  year: z.number().min(1900),
  month: z.number().min(1).max(12),
  hour: z.number().min(0).max(23),
})

app.post('/compute',
  zValidator('json', computeSchema),
  async (c) => {
    const data = c.req.valid('json')  // ✅ validated
    // handle...
  }
)
```

---

## 5. Service Implementations

### svc-astro (Ba Zi computation)

```typescript
import { buildFourPillars, getHehunScore } from '@zhop/astro-core/ganzhi'

app.post('/compute-hehun',
  zValidator('json', hehunSchema),
  async (c) => {
    const { person1, person2 } = c.req.valid('json')
    
    try {
      const score = getHehunScore(person1, person2)
      return c.json({ score, interpretation: 'Compatible' })
    } catch (err) {
      logger.error('Hehun computation failed', { error: err })
      return c.json({ error: 'Computation failed' }, 500)
    }
  }
)
```

### svc-signal (Internal Signal Relay)

```typescript
import { createLogger } from '@zhop/logger'

const logger = createLogger('svc-signal')

app.post('/signals/heartbeat',
  zValidator('json', heartbeatSchema),
  async (c) => {
    const payload = c.req.valid('json')
    const response = await c.env.SVC_API.fetch('http://internal/signals/heartbeat', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'content-type': 'application/json',
        'x-internal-key': c.env.INTERNAL_KEY,
      },
      body: JSON.stringify(payload),
    })
    if (!response.ok) throw new HTTPException(response.status, { message: 'Upstream failed' })
    logger.info('Forwarded heartbeat signal')
    return c.json({ ok: true })
  }
)
```

### svc-mailer (Transactional Email via AWS SES)

```typescript
import { SESv2Client, SendEmailCommand } from '@aws-sdk/client-sesv2'

app.post('/send',
  zValidator('json', mailSchema),
  async (c) => {
    const { to, subject, html } = c.req.valid('json')
    
    const ses = new SESv2Client({
      region: c.env.AWS_REGION,
      credentials: {
        accessKeyId: c.env.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID,
        secretAccessKey: c.env.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY,
      },
    })
    const result = await ses.send(
      new SendEmailCommand({
        FromEmailAddress: c.env.AWS_SES_FROM,
        Destination: { ToAddresses: [to] },
        Content: {
          Simple: {
            Subject: { Data: subject },
            Body: { Html: { Data: html } },
          },
        },
      }),
    )
    
    return c.json({ messageId: result.MessageId })
  }
)
```

### svc-notify (FCM Push)

```typescript
import { initializeApp, cert } from 'firebase-admin/app'
import { getMessaging } from 'firebase-admin/messaging'

const app = new Hono()

app.post('/send-multicast',
  zValidator('json', notifySchema),
  async (c) => {
    const { tokens, title, body } = c.req.valid('json')
    
    const messaging = getMessaging()
    const response = await messaging.sendMulticast({
      tokens,
      notification: { title, body },
      data: { type: 'reading_update' },
    })
    
    return c.json({
      successCount: response.successCount,
      failureCount: response.failureCount,
    })
  }
)
```

### svc-admin-notify (Telegram Alerts)

```typescript
import { createLogger } from '@zhop/logger'

const logger = createLogger('svc-admin-notify')

app.post('/notify',
  zValidator('json', notifySchema),
  async (c) => {
    const { text } = c.req.valid('json')
    const url = `https://api.telegram.org/bot${c.env.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}/sendMessage`
    const response = await fetch(url, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'content-type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({
        chat_id: c.env.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID,
        text,
        parse_mode: 'HTML',
      }),
    })
    if (!response.ok) {
      logger.error('Failed to deliver Telegram alert', { status: response.status })
      throw new HTTPException(500, { message: 'Notification failed' })
    }
    return c.json({ ok: true })
  }
)
```

